# Server & API Routes

- Single `server.ts` file at project root — keep it self-contained
- Uses `tsx` to run TypeScript directly (no compilation step)
- In production, serves Vite build from `dist/`

## API routes

- `POST /api/transform` — Claude (Anthropic SDK) transforms prompt → editorial JSON
- `POST /api/generate` — Gemini (Google GenAI SDK) generates image from `prompt_compiled`

## Error handling pattern

```typescript
catch (error: unknown) {
  console.error("Route error:", error);
  const msg = error instanceof Error ? error.message : "Unknown error";
  res.status(500).json({ error: `Description: ${msg}` });
}
```

## Environment variables

- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` — required for Claude
- `GEMINI_API_KEY` — required for Gemini
- `GEMINI_IMAGE_MODEL` — optional override (default: `gemini-2.0-flash-preview-image-generation`)
- `PORT` — server port (default: 3001, Railway assigns automatically)

## Claude response parsing

Always strip markdown fences before parsing — Claude occasionally wraps JSON in backticks despite instructions:

```typescript
let jsonText = textBlock.text.trim();
if (jsonText.startsWith("```")) {
  jsonText = jsonText.replace(/^```(?:json)?\n?/, "").replace(/\n?```$/, "");
}
const data = JSON.parse(jsonText);
```
